      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CRIPPA (5) made a good impression on debut last week over 1690m at Maryborough, coming from one spot wider to beaten just 2 metres into second. Open to natural improvement. Leading hope. JACWILL KID (1) is a colt by Huntsville making his debut for the Geoff Webster yard. Has the benefit of the ace draw and has produced some decent trial efforts so expect he will be ready to run a big race. Stablemate LA CANTATRICE (2) was beaten just 2.2m into third at Maryborough at her first racetrack appearance. Strips fitter and draws well so can make her presence felt again. ROCKLEIGHS LEGACY (8) draws for a trail and may improve off the debut fourth.",
